<h2>Eric Metcalf Seats for Students</h2>
 
<p>If interested let Mr Biasi know, 
so that he can contact Dave Albert directly.  
Please do not contact him yourself.

<p>This is for all middle and high, band, choir and orchestra teachers,
and is another opportunity to offer Wake Co Schools. It only involves
a student and parent or teacher each concert, but goes through the
entire 14 Concerts of the Classical Series. Ideally, we would like to
see someone enjoy these seats that would not otherwise be able to
attend a concert.

<p>following from Dave Albert:
 
<blockquote>
<p><i>I am pleased to offer an opportunity for Band, Choir, Orchestra or
Piano Educators, for one of your students and either you or their
parent to attend a Friday night, Raleigh Classical Series Concert in
Meymandi Concert Hall, Raleigh, NC. The opportunity is The North
Carolina Symphony Eric Metcalf Seats for Students.</i>
 
<p><i>Eric Metcalf was a local young man of exceptional promise whose life
was cut short by a tragic rock climbing accident in July 2012. Eric’s
parents, Jim Metcalf and Kim Berthiaume, and their older son, Steve,
had been thinking of appropriate ways to honor Eric and his passions.
Because of Eric’s love of classical music, his own notable musical
accomplishments, and his regular attendance at North Carolina Symphony
concerts, it seemed fitting to provide opportunities that would
support the programs he would have loved and that would create a
lasting legacy.</i>

<p><i>His family has established the North Carolina Symphony Eric Metcalf
Seats for Students Fund.  Eric often commented on how fortunate he was
to be able to attend North Carolina Symphony concerts and wished that
young people without the financial means could also attend concerts.
This endowed fund will provide seats for Friday night Classical
Concerts in Raleigh for a select number of students and their parent
or guardian. Information about the program is located here:</i>

<blockquote>
<i><a href="http://www.ncsymphony.org/blog/index.cfm/2013/4/12/eric-metcalf-seats-for-students-fund">Eric Metcalf Seats for Students Fund</a></i>
</blockquote>
 
<p><i>The Classical Concerts Series offers a variety of Orchestra Music
featuring Full Orchestra, Piano, Solo and Chamber Vocal, Solo and
Chamber Instrumental, and Major Choral works. A list of the concerts,
when they are and what is featured is located here:</i>

<blockquote>
<i><a href="http://www.ncsymphony.org/subscriptions/concerts.cfm?id=141">Raleigh Classical Series</a></i>
</blockquote>
 
<p><i>The first concert, Friday 20 Sept has been filled but all others are
open. We would like to offer these seats for a student of yours and
their parent, or you if the parent cannot attend.    This is a
wonderful opportunity offered by the Metcalf family. I hope that your
student will enjoy the concert and I know the Metcalf family will
enjoy knowing their efforts are continuing Eric’s love of music and
wishes for other to enjoy the same.</i>
 
<p><i>David S. Albert
<br>Director of Education
<br>North Carolina Symphony</i>
</blockquote>

